    <h3>Dungeons assembled at runtime</h3>
    <p>Rooms were built from a layout data asset that defined connectivity, encounter density, and trap placement. A failsafe layer in the Game Instance retried generation when a layout dead-ended — players never saw the seam. Each room was its own little machine of triggers, traps, and goblin merchants.</p>
