<section class="section narrow">
  <h2>What I learned by stopping</h2>
  <p>The market analysis came too late. By the time I was deep enough into Steam tag data and concurrent-player charts to see the saturation clearly, I had six months of work in the project. The hard call was admitting that more polish wouldn't fix a positioning problem.</p>
  <p>Concluding it taught me to do market research first and the engineering second — which I'd known intellectually for years, and now know in my bones. The post-mortem on the devlog goes into the numbers.</p>
  <p><a href="/devlog/goblins-greed-postmortem/" style="color: var(--accent-gg); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(184,157,203,0.4); text-decoration: none; padding-bottom: 1px;">Read the full post-mortem on the devlog →</a></p>
</section>

